<item>
            <title>[LU-1345] Handle none integer values in sanity 215 test</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1345</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sanity test 215 tests the values that come out of various /proc/sys/lnet/* files. The test validates the format that is expected. If your test setup has improper routes you can get a NA value instead of a integer which is not handled by the test. This is my case for /proc/sys/lnet/routers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cat /proc/sys/lnet/routers &lt;br/&gt;
ref  rtr_ref alive_cnt  state    last_ping ping_sent deadline down_ni router&lt;br/&gt;
3          1         1     up            7         1       NA      -2 10.37.202.56@o2ib1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a simple patch to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.X test suite</environment>
